 <h2>Hotel vs. Airbnb in Vernal — What to Consider</h2>
 <p>Airbnbs and VRBOs in Vernal can be a good option for large groups or very long stays — but they come with trade-offs that travelers don't always think about until they arrive. There's no front desk if you have a problem at midnight. No breakfast — you're cooking or eating out every meal. No daily housekeeping. And cancellation policies vary wildly by host. For stays under 30 days, a hotel with weekly rates, included breakfast, and a front desk is usually the simpler, safer, and often cheaper choice when total cost is calculated.</p>
 <ul class="feat-list">
  <li>Hotels offer consistency — Airbnbs vary dramatically by host</li>
  <li>Free breakfast at a hotel saves $10–$15/person/day vs. cooking or dining out</li>
  <li>24-hour front desk handles problems — no waiting for a host to respond</li>
  <li>Daily housekeeping keeps rooms clean without effort</li>
  <li>Hotels handle their own maintenance — no broken AC surprises</li>
  <li>Flexible cancellation policies at Best Western Vernal Inn</li>
 </ul>
</div>
